[Method]
SetExpandedImage
[Prefix]
Odcl_Tree_
[Desc]
This method assigns an image from the image list as the image to be displayed once tree item has been expanded. \par \par \b1 Please note! \b0 Items with \cf1 String Keys \cf0 attached to them \b1 can \b0 have expanded images. Also note that this call must be made before the tree item is expanded. The best coding practice would be to call this method just after the required tree item has been added to the tree control.
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab Key
[as String or Long]
\par\tab ExpandImageIndex
[as Integer]


[Method]
GetExpandedImage
[Prefix]
Odcl_Tree_
[Desc]
This method retrieves the index of an assigned image in the tree control’s image list that is to be the image to be displayed once the tree item has been expanded. If a node item does not have a \cf1 String Key \cf0 assigned to it, it will not have an expanded image.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
ProjectFileName
\par\tab Key
[as String or Long]


[Method]
ExpandItem
[Prefix]
Odcl_Tree_
[Desc]
This method expands any visible node item to display its children. \par
\par \b ExpandStyle Flags:
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 \b Flag \tab Description \b0
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 -1 \tab Collapses the tree branch.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 0 \tab Toggles the tree branch from expanded to collapsed or collapsed to expanded.	
\par \pard\fi-710\li710 1 \tab Expands the tree branch.	
\par \pard\fi-0\li0
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab Key
[as String or Long]
\par\tab ExpandStyle
[as Integer]


[Method]
DeleteItem
[Prefix]
Odcl_Tree_
[Desc]
This method deletes any tree item and its children. \par \par \b1 Please note! \b0 If the tree control was populated using \cf1 String Keys \cf0, this method may incorrectly re-order the internal Key list so that \cf1 String Keys \cf0 will not match the correct node items. This is a design flaw of the Microsoft Tree control and a work around has not be found.

[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab Key
[as String or Long]


