ProjectFileName
\par\tab ParentKey
[as String or Long]


[Method]
AddChild (Using Lists)
[Prefix]
Odcl_Tree_
[Desc]
This method adds a child tree item to a top level tree item or other child tree item. 
\par \par \b Note:\b0 \par Create list in the manor shown as follows: \par 
          (List (List x y ...) (List x y ...) ...)
\par We have found ObjectARX does not always like lists created as follows:
\par          '(x y ...) (x y ...) ...  \par \par \b1 Please note! \b0 Adding node items with \cf1 String Keys \cf0 attached to them \b1 can \b0 have expanded images. 
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
[Begin List]
\par\tab ParentKey
[as String or Long]
\par\tab Text 
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 Key 
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 ImageIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 SelectedImageIndex 
[as Integer]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 ExpandedImageIndex
[as Integer]
[End List]
\par\tab ...
[End List]



[Method]
AddChild (Without Lists)
[Prefix]
Odcl_Tree_
[Desc]
This method adds a child tree item to a top level tree item or other child tree item. A child is a tree item that is connected to a parent or owner tree item. This method returns the long integer value of the new node item key. \par \par \b1 Please note! \b0 Adding node items with \cf1 String Keys \cf0 attached to them \b1 can \b0 have expanded images. 
[Arguments Return] as Long
ProjectFileName
\par\tab ParentKey
[as String or Long]
\par\tab Text 
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 Key 
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 ImageIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 SelectedImageIndex 
[as Integer]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 ExpandedImageIndex
[as Integer]



[Method]
InsertAfter
[Prefix]
Odcl_Tree_
[Desc]
This method adds a child tree item or top level tree item after an indicated tree a child tree item or top level. This method returns the long integer value of the new node item key. \par \par \b1 Please note! \b0 If the tree control was populated using \cf1 String Keys \cf0, this method may incorrectly re-order the internal Key list so that \cf1 String Keys \cf0 will not match the correct node items. This is a design flaw of the Microsoft Tree control and a work around has not be found.
 \par \par \b1 Please note! \b0 Adding node items with \cf1 String Keys \cf0 attached to them \b1 can \b0 have expanded images. 
[Arguments Return] as Long
ProjectFileName
\par\tab ReferenceKey 
[as String or Long]
\par\tab Text 
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 Key 
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 ImageIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 SelectedImageIndex 
[as Integer]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 ExpandedImageIndex
[as Integer]




