AddParent (Using Lists)
[Prefix]
Odcl_Tree_
[Desc]
This method adds a multiple top level tree items.
\par \par \b Note:\b0 \par Create list in the manor shown as follows: \par 
          (List (List x y ...) (List x y ...) ...)
\par We have found ObjectARX does not always like lists created as follows:
\par          '(x y ...) (x y ...) ... \par \par \b1 Please note! \b0 Adding node items with \cf1 String Keys \cf0 attached to them \b1 can \b0 have expanded images. 
[Argument]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
[Begin List]
\par\tab Text 
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 Key 
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 ImageIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 SelectedImageIndex 
[as Integer]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 ExpandedImageIndex
[as Integer]
[End List]
\par\tab ...
[End List]



[Method]
AddParent (Without Lists)
[Prefix]
Odcl_Tree_
[Desc]
This method adds a top level tree item. This is a tree item that is not connected to a parent or owner tree item. This method returns the long integer value of the new node item key. \par \par \b1 Please note! \b0 Adding node items with \cf1 String Keys \cf0 attached to them \b1 can \b0 have expanded images. 
[Arguments Return] or Long
ProjectFileName
\par\tab Text 
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 Key 
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 ImageIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 SelectedImageIndex 
[as Integer]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 ExpandedImageIndex
[as Integer]

